392. Is Subsequence
Problem
Given two strings s and t, return true if s is a subsequence of t, otherwise return false.

A subsequence can be formed by deleting some (or no) characters without changing the order of the remaining characters.

Example
s = "abc"
t = "ahbgdc"

Output: true
s = "axc"
t = "ahbgdc"

Output: false
Intuition

Use Two Pointers:

i → traverses s
j → traverses t

Whenever characters match, move i.
Always move j.

If i reaches the end of s, all characters were found in order.

Algorithm
Initialize i = 0, j = 0.
While i < s.length() and j < t.length():
If s.charAt(i) == t.charAt(j), increment i.
Increment j.
Return i == s.length().

Java Solution
class Solution {
    public boolean isSubsequence(String s, String t) {
        int i = 0, j = 0;

        while (i < s.length() && j < t.length()) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == t.charAt(j)) {
                i++;
            }
            j++;
        }

        return i == s.length();
    }
}

Dry Run
Example
s = "abc"
t = "ahbgdc"

| i | j | s[i] | t[j] | Match? | i After |
| - | - | ---- | ---- | ------ | ------- |
| 0 | 0 | a    | a    | Yes    | 1       |
| 1 | 1 | b    | h    | No     | 1       |
| 1 | 2 | b    | b    | Yes    | 2       |
| 2 | 3 | c    | g    | No     | 2       |
| 2 | 4 | c    | d    | No     | 2       |
| 2 | 5 | c    | c    | Yes    | 3       |

i == s.length() → true

Complexity
Time: O(|t|)
Space: O(1)
Key Trick
Match → move both pointers
No Match → move only t pointer

When all characters of s are matched in order:

i == s.length()

⇒ s is a subsequence of t.
